When we look into the top-2 SPARQL queries we find that only about 3% of the queries provide equivalent answers. These however, cannot be considered Synonyms by definition since they are always query equivalent reformulations. Typical relations are spouse and sibling such that the reformulations {{2209.07250_FO0036||FO}} and {{2209.07250_FO0037||FO}} are symmetric and the answer sets are identical but no additional semantic context is obtained.